<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="302" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1657,1754]" pageId="1" pageNumber="302">
<emphasis box="[151,273,1657,1682]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="302" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1657,1682]" pageId="1" pageNumber="302">Diagnosis</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
This genus belongs to the Filistatinae and differ from other Neotropical filistatids by great size (
<quantity metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="0.7" pageId="1" pageNumber="302" unit="mm" value="16.0" valueMax="25.0" valueMin="7.0">7–25 mm</quantity>
), calamistrum with setae on the sulcated area, conspicuous fovea, tarsal spines, and male palp with elongated tibiae and cymbium not fused to the tegulum (
<bibRefCitation author="Ramirez, M. J. &amp; Grismado, C. J." box="[667,976,1729,1754]" pageId="1" pageNumber="302" pagination="319 - 349" refId="ref12962" refString="Ramirez, M. J. &amp; Grismado, C. J. (1997) A review of the spider family Filistatidae in Argentina (Arachnida, Araneae), with a cladistic reanalysis of filistatid genera. Entomologica scandinavica, 28, 319 - 349." type="journal article" year="1997">Ramírez &amp; Grismado 1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ramirez, M. J. &amp; Grismado, C. J." box="[988,1049,1729,1754]" pageId="1" pageNumber="302" pagination="79 - 83" refId="ref13010" refString="Ramirez, M. J. &amp; Grismado, C. J. (2008) Filistatidae. In: Claps, L. E., Debandi, G. &amp; Roig-Junent, S. (Eds.), Biodiversidad de Artropodos Argentinos. Buenos-Aires, 2, 79 - 83" type="journal article" year="2008">2008</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
